<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Andrea Pirlo started his tenure as Juventus manager with a 3-0 victory over Sampdoria.</p>

<p>Dejan Kulusevski put Juventus ahead in the 13th minute, with Leonardo Bonucci also scoring in the 78th minute.</p>

<p>Ronaldo, who had earlier hit the crossbar, added a third for Juventus late on. </p>

<p>More to follow...</p>

<p>Andrea Pirlo oversaw a 1-0 victory versus Sampdoria in his first game as Juventus manager</p>

<p>Dejan Kulusevski is congratulated by his team-mates after putting Juventus in the lead</p>

<p>Cristiano Ronaldo struck the crossbar and later managed to get on the scoresheet himself</p>

<p>1000 Juventus supporters were permitted to attend the club's opening Serie A fixture</p>

<p>Juventus: Szczesny; Danilo, Bonucci, Chiellini; Cuadrado, Rabio, McKennie, Frabotta; Ramsey; Kulusevski, Ronaldo</p>

<p>Sampdoria: Audero; Bereszynski, Tonelli, Colley, Augello; Ekdal; Deapaoli, Thorsby, Jankto, Lens; Bonazzoli</p>
